complexity:{tier:4,cat:'cs',label:'Complexity Theory',
desc:'P, NP, NP-completeness (Cook-Levin theorem), polynomial hierarchy, PSPACE, IP=PSPACE, BPP, #P, circuit complexity, interactive proofs, PCP theorem, derandomisation, average-case complexity.',
figures:'Cook (NP-completeness, 1971), Karp (21 reductions), Levin (Soviet, independent NP), Razborov, Impagliazzo, Shamir (IP=PSPACE, 1992)',
jonathan:'You know NP-completeness from ICPC. Now understand why P≠NP is hard to prove, what circuit lower bounds mean, and what IP=PSPACE says about proof systems.',
pre:['computability','combinatorics','graph_theory'],
books:[
  {t:'Computational Complexity: A Modern Approach',a:'Arora & Barak',n:'Free online. Definitive graduate text.',hard:true},
  {t:'Computers and Intractability',a:'Garey & Johnson',n:'The NP-completeness bible. Every reduction.'},
  {t:'Complexity and Real Computation',a:'Blum, Cucker, Shub & Smale',n:'BSS model. Rigorous. Advanced.',hard:true},
],lec:[
  {t:'Arora & Barak: Complexity (free draft)',u:'https://theory.cs.princeton.edu/complexity/',type:'book-free'},
  {t:'Ryan O\'Donnell: Complexity (CMU YouTube)',u:'https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLm3J0oaFux3YL5vLXpzOyJiLtqLp6dCW2',type:'video'},
]},

prob_theory:{tier:4,cat:'math',label:'Probability Theory (Rigorous)',
desc:'Measure-theoretic probability: (Ω,ℱ,P), random variables, expectation as Lebesgue integral, L^p spaces, characteristic functions, Law of Large Numbers (strong), Central Limit Theorem, conditional expectation as projection, martingales, Markov chains.',
figures:'Kolmogorov (axioms, Grundbegriffe, 1933 — the founding text), Chebyshev, Markov, Lyapunov (CLT), Doob (martingales), Lévy',
jonathan:'All of ML theory, information theory, and statistical learning is on top of this. Kolmogorov\'s 1933 monograph is 84 pages. Read it after doing measure theory.',
